   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "There is no change in behavior. This just helps prepare for the transition from `boost::filesystem::path` to `std::filesystem::path` by adding explicit path <-> string conversion functions which are needed due to a lack of a `boost::filesystem::path::imbue` equivalent in `std::filesystem`.\r\n\r\nAnother benefit of this change is getting rid of implicit conversions between strings and paths so they can be reviewed more carefully and avoided where they are not necessary.\r\n\r\nA detailed description of the problem with windows path encoding ambiguities and the followup to be implemented with the transition away from boost can be found in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/20744#issuecomment-916627496.",
